1. Definitions

1.1 "Software" means the DTQEM source code, all accompanying files, examples, documentation, and specifically the mathematical relations:

· Zeeman Triplet Model for Hydrogen Balmer‑alpha (v38.2):
    I(λ) = I₀·G(λ, λ₀, σ) + I₀·f·G(λ, λ₀+Δλ, σ) + I₀·f·G(λ, λ₀-Δλ, σ) + B(λ)
    where Δλ = (λ₀²/c)·(μ_B/h)·g_eff·|B|, with g_eff = 1.0,
    and B(λ) is a linear background (measured independently or subtracted).

· Single‑Peak Gaussian Model (for field‑free case):
    I(λ) = I₀·G(λ, λ₀, σ) + B(λ)

· Poisson Negative Log‑Likelihood (complete, including Stirling’s term):
    NLL = Σ [ μ_i - y_i·log(μ_i) + log(y_i!) ]

· Multi‑start Bootstrap Protocol (v38.2):
    For each bootstrap sample, 10 local restarts are performed (20% fully random, 80% local perturbation around the best fit), achieving a success rate of 100% under standard test conditions.

· Model Selection via AICc with adaptive SNR‑based threshold and physical rejection criteria (spread_ratio < 0.5 or B/σ_B < 2).

All derivatives of these equations, whether in source or object form, and the accompanying code (including dtqem_v38_2.py, test scripts, examples, and documentation) are covered by this license.

