8. Additional Provisions for v38.2 (Zeeman Inversion for Hα)

8.1 The Zeeman inversion methodology (including the triplet Gaussian model, Poisson likelihood, AICc‑based model selection, and the multi‑start bootstrap protocol with 10 restarts, 10% perturbation, and 20% fully random starts) is an integral part of the Software and is subject to the same license terms.

8.2 Users are strongly encouraged to report any errors or improvements to the author to benefit the research community.

8.3 The author reserves the right to publish updated versions under the same or a compatible license.

8.4 Key improvements in v38.2 compared to v34.2 (as reflected in this license):

· Bootstrap success rate raised from ~98% to 100% (under standard test conditions).
· Increased n_restarts to 10, added 20% fully random starts to escape local minima.
· Introduced physics‑based acceptance criterion (B ≥ 0, sigma > 0, amplitude > 0) instead of relying on scipy’s success flag.
· Added automatic model selection using AICc with SNR‑dependent threshold and physical rejections (spread_ratio < 0.5 or B/σ_B < 2).
· Full support for Hydrogen Balmer‑alpha (Hα) line analysis.

